{{Top|canon=Comm/scan processor}}
{{Youmay|the computer system|[[Com-Scan]], the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' department}}
[[File:Torryns_tool.png|thumb|right|250px|[[Toryn Farr/Legends|Toryn Farr]] using a tool to interface with the com-scan display map]]

A '''com-scan''', or '''comm/scan''', was a computer system which controlled and integrated the hundreds of complicated communication and sensor systems, from [[Electro photo receptor|electro-photo receptors]] and [[Full-spectrum transceiver/Legends|full-spectrum transceivers]] to [[Dedicated energy receptor/Legends|dedicated energy receptors]] and [[Subspace transceiver/Legends|subspace transceivers]], found aboard large [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]] like [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyers]]<ref name="EGWT">''[[The Essential Guide to Weapons and Technology]]''</ref> (located inside the conning tower's [[sensor globe]]s<ref name="ITW:OT">''[[Inside the Worlds of Star Wars Trilogy]]''</ref>) and [[Mon Calamari Star Cruiser/Legends|Mon Calamari Star Cruisers]].<ref name="EGWT" />

==Description==
Com-scans consisted of rows of [[Computer/Legends|computer]] consoles, augmented by both flatscreen monitors and [[Holoprojector/Legends|holoprojectors]] to display data such as [[Fleet/Legends|fleet]] movements and battle simulations. The units were staffed by highly skilled [[Communications officer/Legends|communications]] and [[Sensor officer/Legends|sensor officers]] to evaluate the data, assisted by [[Droid/Legends|droids]] programmed with complex data-sorting algorithms. They decided which data was important enough to pass on to the command staff.<ref name="EGWT" />

Com-scan [[Computer/Legends|computers]] processed and analyzed information from [[Sensor array/Legends|sensor arrays]], such as those found aboard [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]]. [[Starship/Legends|Starships]] had a wide range of [[Sensor/Legends|sensors]], including long-range [[electro photo receptor]]s, [[Full-spectrum transceiver/Legends|full-spectrum transcievers]], [[Dedicated energy receptor/Legends|dedicated energy receptor]]s, and [[broadband transceiver]]s. The com-scan collated all the data, allowing the operator to potentially detect starships or hidden bases. Readings matching preprogrammed warning conditions activated reserve sensor banks for a more detailed investigation. These conditioned included detecting power fluctuations indicating the presence of a ship, or energy spikes from a [[Power generator/Legends|power generator]] hidden by stealth systems.<ref name="EGWT" />

==History==
The [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]] used a com-scan computer during the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] to remotely assist Rebel [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] when their sensors were jammed by the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|DS-1 Orbital Battle Station]].<ref name="EGWT" /> It was able to identify enemy units during the engagement.<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref>

The [[Executor/Legends|''Executor'']] used com-scan systems upon entering the [[Hoth system/Legends|Hoth system]] to verify the location of [[Echo Base/Legends|Echo Base]] on the [[Star system/Legends|system's]] [[Hoth/Legends|sixth planet]] by detecting a [[Deflector shield/Legends|energy shield]]. During the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], [[General/Legends|General]] [[Carlist Rieekan/Legends|Rieekan]] and his command staff used a [[MicroThrust Processors]] [[OrC-19 com-scan integrator console]] to monitor [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] forces and coordinate the ground defense and evacuation efforts.<ref name="EGWT" />

Much smaller com-scan computers, such as the [[CO-0012]], could also be found on military command vehicles, like the [[LAVr QH-7 Chariot]].<ref name="EGWT" />

Both [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn]] and the reborn [[Palpatine/Legends|Emperor]] used com-scan computer systems during their respective campaigns to bring down the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]].<ref name="EGWT" />

